title: Start
body:
Kira: Sigh. Of course this would happen now. Locked out, and no key in sight. Great, just great.
Kira: Okay, think. I had the key when I left... somewhere. Maybe I dropped it when I jumped over that gap? Or was it when I climbed the tree? Ugh, focus! I can't get back in without that key.
Kira: Right, no time to waste. I just need to retrace my steps. Come on, key, where are you?
